      description:
          "Christmas is an annual festival commemorating the birth of Jesus Christ, observed primarily on December 25 as a religious and cultural celebration among billions of people around the world. Shiny stars and sparkling lights take over the land in December, as God’s Own Country prepares itself joyously for the coming of Christmas. Houses and streets are decked beautifully as the State celebrates this beloved occasion with fervour.\n\n Solemn services take place at churches across the State along with widespread revelry that continues right up to the coming of the New Year. People of all communities come together, elaborate cakes and gifts are exchanged, and general mood of happiness and tranquillity comes over the entire populace. It is a merry time for everyone alike, with the message of love and harmony echoing off every corner of the State.",
